body:
Consider the following example based on some code I wrote:

```verilog
module example(input [63:0] i, output [63:0] o);
wire tmp;
assign tmp = i & 64'hFEFEFEFEFEFEFEFE;
assign o = i & -i;
endmodule
```

Here, Yosys should notice that carries can neither propagate nor generate from one byte to the next, and bisect the 64-bit `$alu` cell into 8 8-bit `$alu` cells, drastically shortening the carry propagation delay.

It's also possible that in the middle of a `$alu` there's a generate term (e.g. 1+1). The `$alu` cell could be bisected at that point too.

